<div id="foogallery-gallery-732" class="foogallery-container foogallery-owl-carousel foogallery-lightbox-foobox-free owl-carousel hover-effect-zoom  ">

				<div class="foo-item" >
			<a  href="https://uicarchives.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/10/2015/01/DG15_02_08_27.jpg" data-caption-title="40/4 chair first used at Circle campus." data-caption-desc="40/4 chair &#040;pronounced: “40 in four”&#041; designed by David Rowland.&nbsp; Last known remaining chair from the manufacturer&#039;s first order.&nbsp; Circle campus had the first 17,000 chairs sold.&nbsp; Original paper label on bottom from General Fireproofing Company includes Rowland’s signature.&nbsp; Black metal back and seat. &nbsp; Steel legs.&nbsp; Missing&#058; four transparent polycarbonate glides.&nbsp; University of Illinois at Chicago Circle.&nbsp; 2015 Feb 11.&lt;BR&gt;See more about &lt;a href=&quot;https://uicarchives.library.uic.edu/40-4Chair&quot;&gt;40/4 Chair&lt;/a&gt;." data-attachment-id="1325"><img  src="https://uicarchives.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/10/cache/2015/01/DG15_02_08_27/1128012692.jpg" alt="40/4 chair first used at Circle campus." width="150" height="150" /></a>			</div> 
				<div class="foo-item" >
